values:
I've just burnt the strongest and best and most good looking bridge I know of...

I feel empty.

I told the wrong person about the wrong thing and then when it came back to bite my arse I got angry.  I took some petrol to a bridge, lit a match and fell asleep in a drunken stupor.

I hate myself.

The consequences of my actions will probably only affect me.  And Got DAMN does it hurt like a motherfucker.

I've said shit that may or may not be true to my friend Anneka.  She then told my sister because they're closer friends than Anneka and myself are now.  My sister hurt me so much I cried.  I mean, I was bawling!  My housemate, Danielle (who, it turns out, knew Anneka in primary school.  Small world, huh!) was there to comfort me, but I was still so hurt by everything I said things I probably shouldn't of said to Anneka.  Through sms no less.  That's right, I'm chicken shit!

I feel like crap.

I was on close today, 3:30 to 12 am, and every time I got a break, and even before and after work when I was driving all I wanted to do was call her and just talk.  Talk about random shit.  That's what I love.  Talking to Anneka about the most random things because she's there...

But now I've ruined it coz of one bad day following a few rocky months. 

She told my sister things she knew I didn't want her to know, but I'M the one who sent the chicken shit message!  I'M the one who's supposed to be responsible and who usually puts the worst kind of person before herself...

Now I'm lost.

My housemate and I, we're also on rocky grounds.  To cut a long story short... I'm good friends with someone she thinks I shouldn't be.

My friend Lauren and I...  Big Day Out (which ROCKED!!!) wasn't the best time for us.  She was rude and I was cranky... Not. Cool.

The common denominator?  Me!  That's why my sis thinks I'm a drug fucked junkie!  Coz I'm burning all the bridges I see and I can't stand her superiority.  "It's all the drugs."  I'm the loser and she's fucking perfect!  I've just discovered 'fun' and she's responsible and thinks I'm a piece of shit.  No, I don't have to pinging to have fun.  Infact, "drugs are bad, mmmkay?"  I'm over them.  But she thinks they're my entire life.  What Anneka said didn't help.  She made everything worse times a thousand!

 

I'll be 21 in May.  ... It's so depressing I could cry even harder.  Everytime someone brings it up I get teary and walk away.  21 is my scary age.  I haven't done anything with my life (like go overseas or sky dive) and it makes me upset.  I'm going to get so FUCKED UP I can't remember my problems and don't remember I'm OLD for a week!!!  I've told all my workmates.  "You can't let me remember I'm old, ok?  You have to make sure I'm comatose before I go home!  DON'T LET ME REMEMBER!"

I freaked most of them out.

.........  I'm pretty worn out.  Work was nothing, but being pretty damn sure that the best Best Friend you ever had probably hates and/or never wants to see you again is crushing.  I have some alcohol here so I'm going to have it and hopefully pass out before 6 a.m.

Goodnight people.  Learn from the mistakes of others and treasure good friendships.

 

Enjoy Forever!
http://insane-kitty.livejournal.com/56067.html

Ok, so I'm not loving being sun burnt...  Or the fact one of my good mates is being mean to me infront of her highschool friends (childish, I know) and calls me wude names...

But I LUUUURVED the Big Day Out!!!  It made feel all tingly-wingley...  Mainly in my feet coz they got trampled in moshes.  But it was cool. LUUURRRV Faker!  RADNESS!  And enjoyed most of the day....

Then afore mentioned friend left me and our friend Emily and went off to get trashed with her other mates and didn't keep her phone on her.  And nobody else was answering their phones!!!  I had 4 out of 6 numbers, NOBODY ANSWERED!  80 thousand people or whatever, you'd think to keep your phone on you!!

*inhales*

Then Emily and myself bought contacts.  SO cool.  First time I've even worn them (tough cookies, those one) and now I have a red eye from scratching my eye socket...  Yummeh.

I've been in Sydney for *counts* 3 days now.  Staying in a hostel with backpackers and stuff, they're funny.  We'll be chatting to them while out having a smoke or getting air coz we're trashed, and just start talking to people.  I've met Engligh, Irish, Scottish, Swedish, French... and Dickhead.  The Dickheads have a language of their own...  Anyhow, I'm leaving the hostel early coz of this 'friend' giving me the constant shits, but my housemate Danielle, said she'd come pick me up after work, or we could stay at her friends house and chill out.  She said to 'give me time to chill out.'  She's such a sweetie sometimes!  BTW, she finished work at 2:30 am.  So she'll be here at 6-ish... and we're going to blow this popsickle stand and have a damn good time!  She's actually an awsome housemate.  She even taught me how to wake her properly...  Very gently...  She can get very crunky.  VERY Crunky.

That's one of the reasons I came to Sydney, to get away from al the dramas everywhere, but now she's saving me.  I have a lot of time for that girl.  She's been brilliant... most of the time...

In other news:
*Moved house.
*Workmate is pregnant
*I'm quitting smoking with her...
*I'll be requiring 2 tolerant housemates in the next few months
*I'm SO enjoying this trashbag week. 
*I'm now able to ignore mild hangovers from practice
*I'm still learning to be a Duty Manager, but I'm coming along quite nicely... so they say.

Gotta run, time's almost up.

Enjoy Forever!
http://insane-kitty.livejournal.com/55889.html

So, I was gonna be D.M. then I wasn't now early new year... light blue shirt, baby!  You walk into my club and you make trouble I kill ya!!!

I have a crush on the worst person for me to have a crush on right now.  And It's not one of those 'I'll watch from a distance and just admire' things...  No, no.  I'm certain he likes me.  Mainly coz he said it...

But, there is no possible way I could do anything about it because... Uh... because I've been warned indirectly.

Other news, Work is going well.  We had our Christmas party last week and it resulted in many fights, one member of McKellar Soccer Club losing a tooth, one getting fired and much more friction than before.  Of course, the member of staff that got fired shouldn't have said what they said without knowing it'd get back to the boss and expect to get off scott free.  But I was on almost best behavior!  *puffs out chest*  I was peace maker coz I've worked at the Hawker club and they all know me.  At one point I was grabbing my friends in a vice grip and dragging her off....

 

Fun Fun FUN!!!

 

Gotta run!

 

Enjoy Forever!
http://insane-kitty.livejournal.com/55641.html

Have you ever....

Wanted to tell someone: 
Everyone puts so much stock in you, you can do this....
I'm not the only one who knows that you can do so much better...
Why can't you see that you're a wonderful person who's knowledge and skill is wasted on this...
I don't do want to sniff meth with you, and I don't want to fuck you, so please leave me alone!!!!
I don't want to 'get to know you better'!  I know it's just code for sex!

My life is so fucked up.  I'm up for D.M. soon.  This is all speculation, but Naiz is prolly gonna be D.M. soon, so I'm gonna be stand in D.M.  She deserves it, but I fucking don't!!!! Any Tom, Dick and 'I just want to get to know you better' can tell you that!  I'm to immature!  Duty Manager!  Of a club!!!  In my current condition...  How about we ressurect Jesus!



I'm sorry.  I apologise to all Jesus lovers, but I have to say... even if it's just to state the obvious: he's dead.


"OMG!  I can't beleive she just said that."

Well, I said it.

I'm sick of all the bullshit I have to deal with every day.  Even if I sleep all day, there's always bullshit.  I can't get through one Fucking DAY without something being fucked up!

Cryptic make the mind work harder...


*inhales*

So, Peter (my old D.M.) is moving away, Renae will more than likely take his place.  She can handle it better than anyone!  She has the talk, the knowledge...  She can make it.  But!  Does she think she can???  Nope.

Chatting with Matty tonight, he says they're gonna train me up as sub D.M. right?  WRONG!!!  I have the sensibility of a siberian ant.  THAT'S RIGHT! NO ONE KNOW'S WHAT THE FUCK THAT IS!!!!!!  

I just want....  to stop talking about me...?

No, I just want someone to go through the paces, and to say, 'calm down.  You're going to be alright.  You can handle this.  You'll do fine, but just take it one step at a time...'

I want... NO PRESSURE!!!!!!

I WANT TO KNOW WHY I FEEL LIKE SHIT!

I WOULD LIKE TO KNOW WHAT I'M DOIND WRONG!

I WOULD LIKE.... time...  A friend...  To see what I'm doing...  And to walk me through it...


I'm so lost, I can't even finish-

Work was work, you like it or you hate it.  That was that.

 

I have SO much respect for some of the people I work with, it's almost changed my whole perspective on work.  Almost.

Miss Mandy (now known as Top Gun) cut off 4 people last night.  4!!!!!  That's more than people than I've cut off in my whole career.  Only one more, but she's a little person, so her taking charge and being all assertive and stuff was wonderful.  I was so proud I started calling her Top Gun, thus the new nickname.

And Renae...  Well, I've always had alot of time for that woman, but now I have even more respect for her.  She's tops.  And that's big coming from me.

Danni Girl...  We talked and she amazes me.  She's got some stories that leave me slack-jawed, but she's still who she is now and I have massive respect for her, too.

These three bellas, just fun people before, are now so high in my books I can't see them through the clouds.  Massive respect!  Biggest up yourselves, girls! (compliment)

Enjoy Forever!
http://insane-kitty.livejournal.com/55223.html

FUCK FUCK FUCK!!!!!

 

Fucking work, fucking hours, stupid time and I'm SO BORED!  I get to work, I work, I'm bored, I finally leave, I'm done.

No.

*sighs*

They've been calling me in heaps, and I just got my poker machine licence today, so if rumors are true, they're going to train me up as a Duty Manager soon.

I've also recently received: My gambling certificate (I can recognise problem gamblers and help them deal with their situation in times of need.... PFFT!!!!), my drivers licence renewal, my phone bill, my kisschasy cd and a letter from a cancer foundation that's just randomly sent out...

Work Work WORK!!!  It's almost all I freaken do!!!

 

It's bringing me down hardcore, and that shit's just not gangsta!  I'm always tired and I'm sick and I was talking with my sis and we both think I'm DYING!  ... Well, no we don't, but something's up.  I'm going to see the doctor again.  Boo Hoo.  I'm always at the stupid doctors office!

August and September were pretty shitty months, I'll be glad when October is out of the way, too.  I'm looking forward to some kick-back time, but when I'll get it is anyones guess.  Sleep sleep sleep sleep SLEEP!

I think I'm just on a downer right now.  I have work tomorrow, I accidentally forgot about meeting up with a friend tonight and I'm feeling guilty as shit.  I'm in need of sleep and OMG!  MY MUM MET A CHEETAH!  She finally went (it was her birthday present (which was in MAY!!!) and she finally went and there are pictures and I can't wait to see them!!!

Cheetahs rule.

Oh, visit if you're not over-sensitive to weight jokes, or anything of the sort.  It's a mates, and she wanted to put some of the light-hearted jokes out there for others to hopefully muse over.  None of the things said are meant to insult anyone, anyone at all.

Cara sleeps now.

 

Enjoy Forever!
http://insane-kitty.livejournal.com/54914.html

Fuck OFF!  I HATE working reception!  Peter and Theresa, (they're nice... once they're away from work... and not talking about it, or thinking about it...) were my Duty managers today and they both just made my day crap! 

I went to sleep at 3 am last night 'cause I was cleaning my house for the stupid bank appraiser, house maker-look-at-for-leasing-make-the-house-clean, guy...  (Don't.  Ask.)  Then I was woken up by my alarm at 8:20 am so I could vacuum the house... but I decided to fuck it off, and rolled over and was then woken up by Morag AND the guy doing the appraisal on the house wanting to look at the master bedroom... and the ensuite...  AND I was in... something resembling summertime jammies....

Then I had work.  At 10:30.

With Peter.

Who's a bunghole.

Then Theresa came on.

Who's a crazy-head.

...and sometimes talks too much.

 

I almost cried twice today.  I was so worn out and flustered and I couldn't handle everyone talking at me and I just wanted to have a cigarette!

Piper is looking at me.  Fucken' bitch.  She ate my chips.  Her little cat head was in the bag of MY chips crunching away on MY chips and eating my CHIPS!

So!  After I finished shovelling shit (working in reception) I had to go and pick up Annie and her friends and drop them all home.  I was in a LOVELY mood!!!  *coughs*

Then I changed, went back to work and had a few drinks (after my free beer it was all non-alcoholic) to de-stress with the gang and smoke my little lungs out.  That, THAT, my friends, was the best bit of my frikken day! 

I then left, got petrol, went home, and went back to work again to help Naiz with the stackers.  She's helped me so much it seemed fair.

 

 

So... I met a guy the other week and we're meeting up tomorrow for a coffee/drink.  He seems nice but I don't think I have too much in common with him...  except we both don't like serving old people.  I'm just...  Blah... about the whole thing, really.  I'm like, 'right, just another thing to do tomorrow, better shedule it in.'  I'll worry when I'm not surviving on caffine alone...

 

I'm knackered, I'm going to bed.

 

Enjoy Forever!

I'm at work again.  Obvoiusly in reception as there aren't proper computers behind the bar. 

There are people signing in right now.  ... Now they're gone.

I'm so tired!  I keep yawning and then my eyes water and I look like I've been crying.  Early night for me, I think. *sniffs*  Oh, and I'm getting sick.  I don't think my smoking helps much, but just TRY and get me to quit, foo'!
That's right.  Little ol' me is now a smoker.  How dissappointing!  "But Cara, smoking kills!  Every cigarette is doing you damage...  Smoking can harm your pregnant baby (... YOU heard me!) and so on.  I'm so disappointed... Ra Ra Ra...."   Well, Up Yours, Prick! 
*chuckles*  One of my new workmates, Bec, worked behind a bar in Tugga's, and she's got some funny stories to go with her I-don't-get-paid-nearly-enough-to-have-to-put-up-with-your-shit-so-up-yours-prick attitude.  Good Times...

She's making me a coffee right now.  The stupid coffee machine broke down so I couldn't get my morning coffee and the only thing that kept me smiling is the fact I'm incredibly vain and snobbish before my coffee and I'm spitefully making comments about members who've shown up early today that piss me off and who look like complete shit in their old trackies and flannie tops with their beer guts and their bad haircuts and their stupid.... shoes! *inhales*  Mmmmm my coffee has arrived.  *sips*  I still hate half the rude pricks that drink here, but now I'm feeling a little more awake.

What do I feel like for lunch today?  Because I want something from the bistro, but I don't know what they're serving today...  *tummy grumbles hungrily*  I feel like a pie... I think.

I've only done two friggen payouts and I'm bored.  It's sl-

 

 

Matt just walked in and looked around for something then loked at me and left.  I panicked and minimized the screen. 

Ken just arrived.  The Saturday T.A.B. man.  He sits and takes punters bets.  Fucken' punters!

I'm getting tired and I think I'm going to go and order a meal for lunch...  Somehow.

 

 

Enjoy Forever!

My head is POUNDING!  I've got the headache from hell and I can't leave reception and I'm going to DIEEE!!!!!!

I'm so afraid I'll get caught!  I keep checking over my shoulder because I'm afraid Matt (duty manager) will catch me and scold me!

My HEAD!!!!!!!!!!  *cries*

 

I'm getting beter in reception.  I fucked up a couple of times but now I'm totally getting the hang of it all.  I'm all: *gives/takes/checks money* *writes everything down* *calls people* *announces stuff*

It's cool.

 

.....  My paranoia is growing with every sentence, so here I shall leave you.

Stay well, lovelies!

I had my first EVER reception shift tonight.  Collectively I'd done about 2 hours (on my own time, thank-you-very-much) and tonight I did a close shift.  BO-RING!  It was like I'd been shut away in a hole with no contact with civilisation!!!!

Lie.

It was good.  I'd say great, except it was actually boring for most of it.  I balanced the pay-out book (only 1 hiccup!!) and the reception till and the computer pay-outs and the book that records the pay-outs and I made announcements (I got nervous and stammered a little) and I did so well!  I'm not being cocky or anything, I'm just really chuffed!  Theresa came in at close to help show me what I had to fill in, but I found out where and extra dollar came from all by myself and counted all the money and it all added up correctly and I'm really proud of myself.  It's a rare occasion that I'm truly proud of myself.  I hope Jim sees that I didn't fuck up and puts me on a few more shifts.
I'm going to ask him tomorrow if I should get my poker-machine licence.  The club will pay for it, so I don't want to just go and get a photo taken, my prints and a background check done on me for nothing.  But I'm really quite pleased with my progress.  I feel like I'm almost... good. 

The one thing I forgot, the ONE thing.... I forgot to fill out my time sheet.  But I'll do it tomorrow when I go and speak to Jim.  One tiny little oversight and it only concerns me.

I'm going now.

Take care.

I'm so upset!!!!!

 

I realise that I have friend issues...  My past "best friends" have been weird.  It's mucked me around!  I have dependence issues because for how many years my  "best friends" have pushed me around and I have been useless.

Yes!  I go through periods of self-doubt.  For 5 years I went through a period of self-worthlessness.  I haven't had useful suggestions, I've just said what I think [which is useless] and gone with what I've been told.

 

My life right now is fucked up.  I'm so pissed I could hit someone, but I wouldn't because I'm placid... I'm going to watch something and pretend I understand.....

 

 

Laterssss...............

I'm in with the regulars at work.  One of them was talking about doing cones while out fishing and my whole perception of changed!  They're all so cool!  Not because of the cones, but now I've actually stayed and chatted with my favourite little group and realised we have the same humor and stuff, they're so rad! 

... It doesn't matter to me that they're all over 40, because they're fun.  Annie and Owen are my two favs because I've stayed after work and chatted with them alot.  Annie's so nice to me and she asks my opinions on serious matters and considers my advice and confides in me and it's great!  I feel like a grown-up instead of a 20-year-old ex-drama student who's so random she confuses and alienates everyone.

Growing up isn't so bad right now.  Tomorrow I'll fear it again, but right now, it's cool.  It's being responsible and knowing the consequences of all my actions....  Tomorrow it's getting wrinkly and dying without having made anything of my life, but for now I'm happy.

Tomorrow I'm hanging with Josie.  She's completely rad!  I'm picking her up from school (yeah, she's 14/15, so what???) with Anneka and we're going to boost juice.  I haven't been to boost in ages.  I ran into Amy (Josie's sister, whom I know, went to school with and like) and she's still cool.  I love 'em. 

I'm so chuffed at the moment.  Life is sa-weet!  Bits suck, but right now I'm positive.  A good mood, a good.... being awake-ness.... a good vibe.

I'm looking around on the net for a decent feather picture.  The tattoo place didn't have any good ones, so I decided that I'll have to take it upon myself to find myself a good one.  That or design it myself... again.

I'm worn down to a nub.  A nubby-nub.

Two more days of 8 hour shifts and then I am back to a casual casual...  *would stretch out happily if I could move without much pain*

Two of the regulars at work, Annie and Owen (married, and REALLY nice to me) found out today (from me) that I'm going back to casual, oh, and Annie got teary.  I felt so bad!!!  She was saying how she thought I was So strong and her hero and stuff, and I said, 'you're going to think I'm a quitter soon, because as of Sunday evening I'm back to casual.'  Then she got teary.  I like her.  She's SO nice and she always has a bit of a chat to me.

*pouts sadly*

Now I have guilt...

Renae fractured her arm today.  At work, maybe 3 hours before she was meant to start.  She was like, 'I'll still some in to work *is pale and in obvious pain but is a stubborn wench*  I can't lift my arm to drive.' 
Thereasa and I were like, 'fuck off!  You're not coming in, you need to get that checked out and we'll manage without you.  You're in pain and can't work.'

2 more shifts as full time!

 

Sooooo hurty!!

 

G'night.

SAY WHAT!

RONS HOUSE!

*sings more and more*

FREEEEEEEEEEEEE AGENT!  Work is crap and I am happy!  All right, check it, yo!  I talked to Carol (a Duty Manager who'd been off for 3 weeks, but is now back) and said 'I like working here... BUT!  I can't handle working here full time anymore.'  I explained everything and we had a really good chat and she said I should talk to Jimmy (the operations manager).  I did.  My little heart was pounding so hard I almost fainted!!!

So??  So what?  So here's the thing, in two weeks time I'm back as a casual!!!  I said they could teach me to do reception to fill in on short notice, I told them I didn't mind being trained as a DM to cover shifts, I even said I could work upstairs in the bistro.  It's a go.  Woo Hoo!

Why are they being so obliging???  WELL!!!  SO MANY casual are leaving, Adele, the lovely full-time receptionist, is leaving, too, as well as Michelle, a part time receptionist/new bar worker.  They need the people, and I'm willing to stick around, but I just don't want to be full-time anymore.  I am SO happy I can't stop grinning.  I even wrote down my casual shifts today and I just couldn't beleive it happened so fast.  I thought they'd keep me on full-time for another month to 6 weeks, but NOOOOOO!

I'm getting 2 dozen krispy kremes tomorrow.  No sharing!  *drools*

I'm going to go food shopping now.  Life is SWEET!

 

 

Enjoy Forever, munchlins!
http://insane-kitty.livejournal.com/52103.html

Yes.  I have Queer as folk season 2 on dvd now.  My sister is actually going to start looking for the next seasons on the net for me.

Yipee for me!  *prances*

Work is killing me.  I mean that literally.  The aches and pains I feel constantly MUST be that of one who is doomed to die shortly.  AND, to top it all off, to put the cherry on the proverbial cake, I'm never going to go overseas.

That's right.  I'm never going to make it on the fucking plane!  It's all bloody talk, isn't it!?!  If I had the ability to save money, like I actually thought I did, I'd fill in a passport application, get the stupid picture taken, get it all sorted, see a travel agent and LEAVE!  But no.  I can't save a penny.  I'm terrible at this game.  I'm constanly lending out money, I'm constantly needing to buy things, (like food!  Fuck food, I want to travel!) and I must have one of the weakest wills of anybody in Canberra!

I bought QAF, so there's most of my pay gone right there (alot of it goes into a bank I can't touch, but manage to weasle money out of from mum).  I don't regret it, I just wish I didn't need to buy things.  Anything! 

......  I know.  I need my own Sugar Daddy.  ..... One that isn't a total freak.

 

Hmmmmmm.......  This.... was supposed to be a wonderful post about my lovely QAF (which I'm going to watch more of as soon as I finish this), not about money troubles.

 

QAF QAF QAF QAF QAF QAF QAF!!!
